This project runs against the **system** Python 3.12 (`/usr/bin/python3`); its deps
(matplotlib, numpy, pymavlink, mplcursors) live in the user site
`~/.local/lib/python3.12/site-packages`. The environment is PEP 668 externally-managed,
so a plain `pip install` fails with "externally-managed-environment". Install with:

    python3 -m pip install --user --break-system-packages <pkg>

There is no venv and no requirements file (single-script project). A harmless startup
`UserWarning: Unable to import Axes3D` appears from a dual matplotlib install; the
interactive backend is `gtk4agg`.
